  "excerpt": "<img src=\"https://pic2.zhimg.com/v2-cd09a2c3bf6beabe3c455362d0d8c2ab_200x112.jpg\" data-caption=\"\" data-size=\"normal\" data-rawwidth=\"861\" data-rawheight=\"346\" data-watermark=\"original\" data-original-src=\"v2-cd09a2c3bf6beabe3c455362d0d8c2ab\" data-watermark-src=\"v2-9e4b65c3a4e6570cda164febf5a843eb\" data-private-watermark-src=\"\" class=\"origin_image inline-img zh-lightbox-thumb\" data-original=\"https://pic2.zhimg.com/v2-cd09a2c3bf6beabe3c455362d0d8c2ab_r.jpg\"/><a href=\"https://link.zhihu.com/?target=https%3A//notes.andymatuschak.org/zSsjk5UvNPGrYp8B6DEFCMS\" class=\" wrap external\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Execute Program</a> 的课程很少用来提醒先前材料：它们短小而聚焦。每一课都是在这样的假设下写成的：读者已经学过并且<b>记住了</b>所有前置知识。而这个假设也会被阅读环境所强化：<a href=\"https://link.zhihu.com/?target=https%3A//notes.andymatuschak.org/zHLWyC5LVXZLWE9RmoC1gua\" class=\" wrap external\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">在你成功复习其前置课程之前，Execute Program 的课程不会解锁</a>[1]。我向 <a href=\"https://link.zhihu.com/?target=https%3A//notes.andymatuschak.org/Gary_Bernhardt\" class=\" wrap external\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Gary Bernh…</a>",
